edback from the client’s side.\nIf required materials, approvals, or feedback are delayed after the project has been confirmed, the delivery schedule may need to be adjusted accordingly.\nWe will always do our best to accommodate changes to the working period or deadlines when possible. However, this may lead to overlaps with other scheduled work — which, from a karma perspective, is never ideal.\n\nIf delays or changes make the originally agreed timeline unfeasible, Riviera Moretti reserves the right to reschedule the delivery or, if necessary, suspend or terminate the collaboration. In such cases Riviera Moretti cannot be held responsible for delays caused by missing materials, postponed approvals, or changes outside our control.\n\nFrom time to time we may be able to assist with last-minute or emergency requests. Feel free to reach out if you find yourself in a tight situation — we understand that architecture deadlines can occasionally become dramatic. However, emergency availability cannot be guaranteed and should never be assumed.\n\nA project is considered officially booked only once the scope of work, timeline and financial terms have been clearly agreed and confirmed in writing (email confirmation is sufficient). Until such confirmation has been received, Riviera Moretti cannot be considered formally engaged in the project.\n\nIf no confirmation or response is received after an offer has been issued, we will assume that the project will not proceed and our availability may no longer be guaranteed.\n\nClear communication, realistic timelines and mutual respect always lead to the good results.","entityRanges":[],"depth":0}],"flags":{"baseline":true,"calculatedLineHeight":true,"updatedLinks":true,"newListPosition":true},"name":"","text":"","animation":[{"UUID":"70cd2610-f5a2-4632-84cb-f764f2b9afeb","type":"load","steps":[{"duration":2.6,"delay":1.8,"acceleration":"ease-both","from_opacity":0,"use_opacity":true,"opacity":100}],"playOnce":false,"resetWhenOutOfVi